Chapter 2: The Legend of Panjo
2.1 The Story of a Kind Shar-Pei
In the heart of Tbilisi lived an extraordinary Shar-Pei named Panjo.
While other dogs chased cats, Panjo had a unique gift — he could sense when children were sad.
One day, he wandered into a children’s hospital garden and began amusingly wrinkling his nose, clumsily chasing sunbeams.
A little girl, who hadn’t smiled in weeks, laughed for the first time.
2.2 A Symbol of Hope
Doctors called it the “Panjo Effect.”
This Shar-Pei became the first “four-legged clown,” whose presence brought relief beyond medicine.
PNJC is the digital embodiment of Panjo, scaling his kindness across thousands of hospital rooms simultaneously through blockchain technology.
________________________________________
Chapter 3: Social Utility — ClownCare
3.1 The Science of Joy
Laughter therapy is a medically recognized method shown to reduce cortisol levels in children by 30–40%.
The ClownCare program funds professional medical clowns who help children cope with difficult treatments.
3.2 Support Mechanism
PNJC is not just a meme — every ecosystem transaction (liquidity, NFTs, etc.) contributes value to the foundation.
Token holders gain access to On-chain Proof of Charity, where every donated lari is verifiable on the Polygon blockchain.
________________________________________
Chapter 4: Technical Architecture & Security
4.1 Polygon Network (Layer-2)
Polygon was selected to enable scalable charitable transactions:
•	Speed: Near-instant transaction confirmation
•	Cost-efficiency: Fees below $0.01, enabling micro-donations
•	Sustainability: Proof-of-Stake minimizes environmental impact
4.2 Security (OpenZeppelin Standard)
The PNJC smart contract is built using OpenZeppelin, the industry-standard framework.
•	The code is immutable (non-upgradable)
•	No post-deployment interference is possible
________________________________________
Chapter 5: Smart Contract Overview
5.1 PNJC Parameters
•	Total Supply: 1,000,000,000,000 (Fixed)
•	No Mint Function: Supply cannot be increased
•	Zero Tax: 0% buy/sell fees — ideal for exchanges and DeFi aggregators
5.2 Renounced Control
The contract has no owner role, ensuring:
•	No ability to freeze user funds
•	No rule changes post-deployment
PNJC is fully owned by the community and the blockchain itself.
